Mythic 10-4-2016 16:48
I've been extensively thinking about how this lobby system should work in the end
16:49
And let me tell you, it'll get complicated
16:49
We'll want to have everything decentralized, but so they can be hooked together, if that makes sense
16:49
While still keeping it as easy for the users
16:50
So what we have to be prepared for is that
16:50
The server hosting lobby lists is on it's own server
16:50
All lobbies are on different servers
16:50
All games might still be on different server from these lobbies
16:51
But everything will communicate together
16:51
+ you can list your lobby on multiple lobby list servers if you want to
16:51
This'll need some interesting contraptions, but once it works, it'll be beautiful
16:52
For now though, we just want to focus on the decentralized single lobby version, so direct connect by IP with no authentication
16:56
For this purpose, we will have to implement 3 different functionality modes to the lobby server:
  • One for the centralized host, listing other lobbies (and creating it's own)
  • One for standalone lobby server, which can either be used in private or hooked up to centralized hosts to be visible there
  • One for relaying the game boot, this to make it possible to host the lobby and the server on a separate machine
16:57
If anyone has any questions/ideas/thoughs, feel free to share

00:41
Phase 4 system: Master lobby servers have a lobby list of all available lobbies Individual lobby servers can enlist them to a lobby server Master lobby server can host it's own lobbies 3rd party lobbies can enlist themselves on a master lobby server Use cases: As an user, I want to be able to change my nickname on the lobby server As an user, I want to be able to view a list of all lobbies and their information Player count Player limit Lobby name Currently selected gamemode Ping Is the lobby password protected Lobby host's name As an user, I want to be able to join a lobby from the lobby list As an user, I want to retrieve chat history once I've joined the lobby As an user, I want to be able to see other players in the lobby As an user, I want to be able to send chat messages As an user, I want to be able to choose my settings for the game As an user, I want to be able to create a lobby (thus, becoming a lobby host) As a lobby host, I want to be able to change the name of my lobby As a lobby host, I want to be able to view a list of all available game modes As a lobby host, I want to be able to choose a game mode As a lobby host, I want to be able to change my gamemode specific settings As a lobby host, I want to be able to mute other players from chat As a lobby host, I want to be able to kick other players from the lobby As a lobby host, I want to be able to ban other players from the lobby As a lobby host, I want to be able to password protect my lobby As a lobby host, I want to be able to start the game Needs investigation in implementation possibility: As an user, I want to have a friendlist @learn brainfuck these are the use cases I came up with for the lobby client/server system
